                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Announces receipt of book entitled "Modern Reform Examined: or, The Union
                    of North and South on the Subject of Slavery," by Rev. J.C. Stiles, formerly of
                    Richmond.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>"Attempt to Murder"</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>We understand that a gentleman named Armstrong, a dealer in cattle was
                    fired at by some ruffians, whilst he was crossing North Mountain, between the
                    Big and Little Calf Pastures, one night last week. The rifle ball passed through
                    the lapel of Mr. A.'s coat.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Armstrong</ln>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>A man was shot at out in the county.</summary>
            </div>
